[White "Quickstarter Guide"]
[Black "Quickstarter 2 9...Be7"]
[Result "*"]

1. d4 d5 2. Nf3 Nf6 3. e3 e6 4. Bd3 c5 5. O-O Nc6 6. c3
{ We are entering the Colle system, which is defined as the c3-setup. White has a few ideas here, e4 usually being the main one. This is often only achieved when White goes dxc5 and only then e4. Due to the knight being on c6, Black is forced to take with the bishop on c5. Resemblances with the Semi-Slav are obvious and we can say that White is a clear tempo up compared to Black's perspective in the Semi-Slav, and that is often an important detail in sharp positions. }
6... Bd6 7. Nbd2 O-O 8. dxc5 Bxc5 9. b4 Be7
{ A slower approach to this position but also a more solid one in a way. } 10.
Bb2 a6
{ Blacks plan is more positional here and inclined more to a solid approach. }
11. a4 { The most energetic. White does not want to allow ...b5 easily. } 11...
e5 12. e4 dxe4 13. Nxe4
{ Chessable: White's plan is to advance the queenside pawns, b4-b5 and c3-c4.  Full Theoretical Overview }
