1. d4 d5 2. Nf3 Nf6 3. e3 e6 4. Bd3 c5 5. O-O Nc6 6. c3 Bd6 7. Nbd2 O-O 8. dxc5
Bxc5 9. b4 Bd6 10. Bb2 e5 { The principled reaction. } 11. e4 dxe4
{ Black also has other options here. } 12. Nxe4 Nxe4 13. Bxe4 Be6 14. Re1 h6
{ Either this move or g6 will haveto be played at some point due to a possible attack on h7 .Of course,there are other possibilities that have been tested in practice. }
15. a3 a5 { Black forces matters before White is able to push c4. } 16. b5 Ne7
17. c4 { An important resource. } 17... f6 18. Rc1 Qc7 19. Bxb7 Rad8 20. Be4
Bxa3 21. Bxa3 Rxd1 22. Rexd1 Re8 23. Bxe7 Qxe7 24. c5
{ White is better.  Full Theoretical Overview } *

