1. d4 d5 2. Nf3 Nf6 3. e3 e6 4. Bd3 c5 5. O-O Nc6 6. c3 Bd6 7. Nbd2 O-O 8. dxc5
Bxc5 9. b4 Bd6 10. Bb2 e5 11. e4 Bg4 12. Re1
{ It is important to understand that this move comes before h3 ! } 12... Re8
13. exd5 Nxd5 14. Qc2 h6 15. h3 Be6 16. b5 Na5 17. Rad1 Qc7 18. c4
{ Chessable: White isn't worried about ...Nb4 because he can move his bishop out of the way with check. }
18... Nb4 19. Bh7+ Kh8 20. Qe4
{ Chessable: Remember this idea of playing the tempo-gaining Bh7+ and the centralizing Qe4 to enable the queenside pawns' advance!  Full Theoretical Overview }
