[White "Quickstarter Guide"]
[Black "Quickstarter 11 Zukertort 6.b3 vs ...Bd6 ...b6"]
[Result "*"]

1. d4 d5 2. Nf3 Nf6 3. e3 e6 4. Bd3 c5 5. O-O Nbd7 6. b3 Bd6 7. Bb2 O-O 8. Nbd2
b6 { A very natural move. } 9. Ne5 { White should seize this opportunity. }
9... Bb7 10. f4 cxd4 11. exd4 Ne4 12. Qe2 f5 13. Nxe4
{ The theme is worth remembering. } 13... fxe4 14. Bb5 Nxe5 15. fxe5 Be7 16.
Qg4
{ Chessable: The point of White's play starting with 13 Nxe4. Black's central pawns imprison light-squared bishop his light-squared, and White is in time to save his nearly-trapped bishop. The latter may pressure the e6-pawn harder with Qg4-h3 and Be2-g4, then he will relocate other bishop starting with Bb2-c1. White will take the fight to the kingside where Black's light-squared bishop cannot participate.  Full Theoretical Overview }
