[Black "Quickstarter 12 6.Nbd2!?"]
[Result "*"]

1. d4 d5 2. Nf3 Nf6 3. e3 e6 4. Bd3 c5 5. O-O Nbd7 6. Nbd2
{ White remains flexible without revealing his intentions. It is not yet clear if we will see a Colle or a Zukertort. Either way, the knight belongs on d2 in both lines. }
6... Bd6 7. Re1 O-O 8. e4
{ An intriguing idea. In the Colle, White goes c3 first, but this is a more direct attempt. }
8... dxe4 9. Nxe4 Nxe4 10. Rxe4
{ Chessable: Black easily stops White's intended Re4-h4. But the former cannot stop the latter from creating kingside weaknesses anyway. }
10... Be7 11. Qe2 cxd4 12. Rxd4 Bf6 13. Rc4 Nb6 14. Rg4 g6 15. Bh6 Re8 16. Ne5
{ White's pieces are developed and active, which is more than can be said for Black.  Full Theoretical Overview }
