[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "Quickstarter Guide"]
[Black "Quickstarter 14 Zukertort vs 8...Nb4"]
[Result "*"]

1. d4 d5 2. Nf3 Nf6 3. e3 e6 4. Bd3 c5 5. O-O Bd6 6. b3 O-O 7. Bb2 Nc6 8. Nbd2
Nb4
{ A logical response, Black pushes the strong bishop away from its active square. }
9. Be2 b6 10. a3 Nc6 11. Bd3 Bb7 12. Qe2 Rc8
{ Black maintains the tension in the centre. } 13. Rad1
{ Played only once but its a suitable strategy; White centralises his play. }
13... Qe7 14. dxc5
{ Chessable: White starts breaking down Black's center, forcing the pawns to advance and leave holes behind. }
14... bxc5 15. e4 Nd7 16. Rfe1 d4 17. Nc4
{ Chessable: White will play e4-e5 if allowed. If Black prevents the advance by placing a knight on e5, White will exchange knights on e5 and play his pieces towards the kingside, starting with Qe2-h5 and Bc1-f4.  Full Theoretical Overview }
