[White "Quickstarter Guide"]
[Black "Quickstarter 17 Zukertort 9.c4 w/ 10.Rc1 vs. 6...Be7"]
[Result "*"]

1. d4 d5 2. Nf3 Nf6 3. e3 e6 4. Bd3 b6 5. O-O Bb7 6. Nbd2 Be7 7. b3 O-O 8. Bb2
Nbd7 9. c4 c5 10. Rc1
{ A reasonable alternative. The idea is to play against a potential queen on c7. }
10... Rc8 11. Qe2 Rc7
{ This is considered the best here. Nonetheless, the position remains full of life. }
12. Rfd1 Qa8 13. cxd5 Nxd5 14. Ne5
{ This is probably critical here, before Black successfully consolidates with ... Rd8 for example. }
14... Nxe5 15. dxe5 Nb4 16. Bb1 Rd7 17. a3 Nc6 18. Nc4
{ Chessable: White will put a knight on d6 but only after rooks on the d-file are exchanged, reducing the number of pieces with which Black can pressure the knight.  Full Theoretical Overiew }
