[Black "Quickstarter 18 Zukertort Quick c2-c4 vs 6...Bd6"]
[Result "*"]

1. d4 d5 2. Nf3 Nf6 3. e3 e6 4. Bd3 b6 5. O-O Bb7 6. Nbd2 Bd6 7. b3
{ One of the most logical ideas. } 7... O-O 8. Bb2 Nbd7 9. c4
{ We don't play with an early queen to e2 here, as the focus is on different plans. }
9... Ne4
{ An aggressive setup, which is typical for Black in these types of positions. }
10. cxd5 { With a specific plan in mind. There are, of course, other plans. }
10... exd5 11. Ne5 Qe7 12. f4
{ A compelling setup. Exchanging the c-pawn for the e-pawn allows White to create a certain imbalance on the kingside. }
12... Nxd2 13. Qxd2 Nf6 14. Qe2 a5 15. Rf3
{ Chessable: White will delay Black's queenside breakthrough for as long as possible and try to push his pawns to force an opening on the kingside. White should be ready to sacrifice material to realise his kingside ambitions.  Full Theoretical Overiew }
*

