[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "Quickstarter Guide"]
[Black "Quickstarter 20 Zukertort 8...c5 9.dxc5!?"]
[Result "*"]

1. d4 d5 2. Nf3 Nf6 3. e3 e6 4. Bd3 b6 5. O-O Bb7 6. Nbd2 Bd6 7. b3 O-O 8. Bb2
c5 9. dxc5
{ A typical idea for White in the Colle and Zukertort systems. We will see this move pop-up throughout the book. }
9... Bxc5 10. Qe2 Nbd7 11. c4 dxc4 12. Nxc4 Qe7 13. e4 Rfd8 14. e5
{ Chessable: White has no qualms exchanging dark-squared bishops, after which he will support the e5-pawn with f2-f4 and put his knight on d6.  Full Theoretical Overiew }
