[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "Quickstarter Guide"]
[Black "Quickstarter 21 Zukertort 6...Bd6 7.Qe2!?"]
[Result "*"]

1. d4 d5 2. Nf3 Nf6 3. e3 e6 4. Bd3 b6 5. O-O Bb7 6. Nbd2 Bd6 7. Qe2
{ Intending a rapid e4. } 7... Ne4 { A critical response. } 8. b3 O-O 9. Bb2
Nd7 10. c4
{ This move is another particular aspect of these systems, which can be played in many situations and contains many nuances. Here I will deal with this specific move order. }
10... f5
{ With this move, Black wants to place the queen on the rather agressive f6-square. }
11. Rac1 Qf6 12. c5
{ This unusual pawn sacrifice takes us to a rather unusual tactics. } 12...
bxc5 13. dxc5 Qxb2 14. cxd6
{ Chessable: From here, Black will try to prevent the White rook from penetrating by clogging the c-file with pieces  (ex: ...Nc3 and ...Nc5)  . Meanwhile, White will try to inconvenience the Black queen behind enemy lines while angling to break through with the rook.  Full Theoretical Overiew }
