[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "Quickstarter Guide"]
[Black "Quickstarter 22 Zukertort 6...Bd6 7.Qe2!? w/ 10.Ne5"]
[Result "*"]

1. d4 d5 2. Nf3 Nf6 3. e3 e6 4. Bd3 b6 5. O-O Bb7 6. Nbd2 Bd6 7. Qe2 Ne4 8. b3
O-O 9. Bb2 Nd7 10. Ne5
{ A rare sight actually but an interesting one nonetheless. } 10... f5
{ Black has couple of interesting possibilities. } 11. Rad1
{ At this stage, it is not easy to determine where the rooks belong, and this is true for both players. The answer to such a question rarely comes easily in the Zukertort, making it a very complicated opening positionally speaking. }
11... Bxe5 12. dxe5 Ndc5 13. Nf3
{ Black wanted to exchange both on d2 and d3. } 13... a5 14. Nd4 Qe8 15. f3
Nxd3 16. cxd3 Ng5 17. Qd2 { Chessable: Vacating the e2-square. } 17... c5 18.
Ne2
{ The knight is transferred to a healthier square: f4!  Chessable: After the knight's transfer to f4, White will put a rook on the c-file and play to open that file.  Full Theoretical Overiew }
