[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "Quickstarter Guide"]
[Black "Quickstarter 23 Zukertort 7.c4 8.Ba3!?"]
[Result "*"]

1. d4 d5 2. Nf3 Nf6 3. e3 e6 4. Bd3 b6 5. O-O Bb7 6. b3 Bd6
{ Against other moves, White plays similarly or can just transpose to 6 Nbd2 ideas. }
7. c4 O-O 8. Ba3
{ A purely positional idea. Not the most ambitious, but not without danger either. By eliminating thebishop on d6,White wants to focus on attacking Black's centre. Moreover, the bishop might become a dangerous attacking asset for Black. }
8... Bxa3 9. Nxa3 Nbd7 10. cxd5 exd5 11. Rc1 a6 12. Nb1 Re8 13. Nc3 Nf8 14. b4
{ Correct play for when Black hesitates to push ...c5.  Chessable: Next, White will play Qd1-b3 and double the rooks on the c-file, pressuring the c7-pawn.  Full Theoretical Overiew }
