1. d4 d5 2. Nf3 Nf6 3. e3 c6 4. Bd3 Bg4 5. Nbd2 e6 6. O-O Nbd7 7. b3 Bd6 8. c4
{ This is another way of meeting this setup. White hurriedly attacks the centre, delaying the development of his dark-squared bishop. }
8... Qe7 9. h3 Bxf3 10. Nxf3 e5 11. cxd5 e4 12. dxc6 bxc6 13. Nh4
{ Interesting tactical motive. } 13... exd3 14. Nf5 Qf8 15. e4 O-O-O 16. Qxd3
Kb7 17. b4
{ White has decent compensation for the sacrificed piece, reminiscent of many Sicilians!  Full Theoretical Overview }
