[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "Quickstarter Guide"]
[Black "Quickstarter 32 4.Nbd2 cxd4 5.exd4 Nc6 6.Bb5"]
[Result "*"]

1. d4 d5 2. Nf3 Nf6 3. e3 c5 4. Nbd2 cxd4 5. exd4 Nc6 6. Bb5
{ The current World Champion's favorite idea. } 6... e6 7. O-O Bd6 8. c3 O-O 9.
Re1
{ The point of White's play in this case is that the c8-bishop is behind its pawn chain. Hence, the b5-bishop will return to d3 and, with that, White will attain his dream postion. }
9... Qc7 10. Qe2 Nd7 11. Nf1 h6 12. Bd2 Rd8 13. Rad1 a6 14. Bd3
{ Chessable: White will play h2-h3 and Ne3-g3, with h6-sacrifices looming. If Black manages to exchange the g4-knight, say with ...Nd7-f6-xg4, White will recapture with h3xg4 and play g4-g5, using the h6-pawn as a hook.  Full Theoretical Overview }
