[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "Quickstarter Guide"]
[Black "Quickstarter 40 1...Nf6 2.Nf3 b6"]
[Result "*"]

1. d4 Nf6 2. Nf3 b6
{ An offbeat reaction, but considering the rise of 1 d4 Nf6 2 c4 b6, this has to be given some attention. It is an elastic approach; Black keeps his options open. Here, we will deal with some unusual setups and ideas. }
3. e3
{ For obvious reasons, I will gravitate towards Colle-Zukertort ideas as much as possible, which explains 3 e3. It is true that 3 Bg5 is also a serious contender, but I have decided not to include the Torre in this book. }
3... Bb7 4. Bd3 c5 5. O-O g6
{ A surprise that serves the purpose of confusing the opponent. But I question the move's objective validity. }
6. Re1 Bg7 7. e4 cxd4 8. e5 { As far as I know, this is a new idea. } 8... Nd5
9. Be4 Qc8 10. Qxd4 Nc7 11. Bxb7 Qxb7 12. Qh4 Nc6 13. Bh6 O-O 14. Nc3 Ne6 15.
Rad1 Rad8 16. Rd3 { White is having more fun here.  Full Theoretical Overview }
