12. Nxe4 Nxe4 13. Bxe4 Be6
{ 13...f5  A more direct attempt and entertaining attempt for Black fails.  14.Bd5+  Kh8  15.b5  Ne7  16.c4 !  Opening up the position.  Nxd5   16...e4  17.Qd4 !  Rf6  18.Qxf6  gxf6  19.Bxf6#   16...Ng6  17.h4 !  Nxh4  18.Nxe5  Qg5  19.f4  Bc5+  20.Bd4  Bxd4+  21.Qxd4  Qf6  22.Rad1  ±  1-0, 40 moves, Miltner, A. 2402 - Appel, R. 2507, Germany 2004.  17.Qxd5  e4  18.Rad1  Bc7  19.Qc5  Bb6  20.Qa3  Qe8  21.Ng5  h6  22.Rd6 !  hxg5  23.Qh3+  Kg8  24.Bxg7 !!  White wins with an elegant finish. }
