{ Black forces matters before White is able to push c4.   15...Qc7  16.c4 !  Rad8   16...Bxc4  17.Rc1  b5  18.Nd2  ±  17.Qc2  Nd4  18.Bxd4  exd4  19.c5  Be7  20.Rad1  Bf6  21.Nd2  Rfe8  22.Qd3  g6  23.g3  h5  24.Nc4  If Black takes on c4, the opposite coloured bishops favour White. Otherwise, the knight is heading straight to d6. }
