[Black "Conclusion"]
[Result "*"]

1. d4 d5 2. Nf3 Nf6 3. e3 e6 4. Bd3 c5 5. O-O Nc6 6. c3 Bd6 7. Nbd2 O-O 8. dxc5
Bxc5 9. b4
{ This is a sharp line that gives us a reversed Semi-Slav, with an extra tempo. This is a tempting idea as an extra tempo in such a sharp position may have huge consequences and can cause Black a serious headache.Black has two valuable ideas:   A.  9...Be7  is a solid approach, Black is trying to develop with  ...b6  and so on.   B.  9...Bd6  is a much more aggressive setup. Black is trying to support the e5-square. Either to occupy it with a piece, or to push  ...e5  , trying to seize the initiative in the centre. }
