6... Bd6 7. Nbd2 O-O 8. Re1 Qc7 9. e4 dxe4
{ Not taking on d4 doesn't change the general ideas of the position, but it can turn out to be even more dangerous for Black. }
10. Nxe4 b6 { Probably safest. } 11. Nxd6 Qxd6 12. dxc5 Qxc5 13. Be3 Qc7 14.
Qd2 Bb7 15. Bf4 Qc6 16. Rad1
{ White has a small but stable advantage. This position can be compared to some French Defence lines, namely 3 Nd2 c5 4 exd5 Qxd5. }
