{ 8...Nb4  is another way of handling this line for Black. In the position arising after 8  Nbd2.  Black has a few ideas. Generally speaking, he develops in a harmonious way and complex play normally follows.White will use the e5-square to generate attacking chances while Black will try and play along the c-file and eventually transfer his knights to better squares. }
