{ A compelling setup. Exchanging the c-pawn for the e-pawn allows White to create a certain imbalance on the kingside. }
12... Nxd2 13. Qxd2 Nf6 { Another typical attacking idea is } 14. Rf3 a5 15.
Rh3 Ne4 16. Qd1 g6 17. Rc1 f6 18. Bxe4 dxe4 19. Nc4 Bd5 20. f5 g5 21. Rh5
{ with a complex position. White intends to go h4. } *

