dxe5 Nd7 9. Qxd5 e6 10. Qd4 Qg5 11. Nc3 Bc5 12. Qf4 Qxe5 13. Qxe5 Nxe5 14. Bd2
O-O 15. O-O-O Rfd8 16. Be2
{ Admittedly, this wasn't forced but one of the many ideas available. In this particluar position though, I think that White has somewhat better chances in the endgame. The bishop on h5 is not badly placed. Let's explore a little further. }
16... Rd7 17. g4 Bg6 18. f4 Nc6 19. h4 h6 20. h5 Bh7 21. Na4 Be7 22. Bf3 Rbd8
23. Bc3 Rxd1+ 24. Rxd1 Rxd1+ 25. Kxd1 { White has some pressure here. } *

