[White "Systems with ...d5: 3.e3"]
[Black "Conclusion"]
[Result "*"]

{ We have examined possible and logical reactions that Black can use, many of which are in the spirit of the Slav after }
1. d4 d5 2. Nf3 Nf6 3. e3
{ Many players have the Slav in their repertoire. So why not play it against the Colle-Zukertort?  We have seen three Slav-like moves here, plus 3...g6 which is more in the spirit of the Grunfeld.   A.  3...Bf5  , a direct attempt to establish the usual schema.   B.  3...Bg4  , another usual plan.   C.  3...c6  , prophylactic. Black waits before deciding where to put the light-squared bishop.   D.  3...g6  , Black combines the Smyslov line in the Slav with ideas from the Grunfeld.  They may all lead to similar play, but each line beholds its own specific nuances and characteristics. }
*

