1. d4 Nf6 2. Nf3 c5 3. d5
{ I deliberately analysed the Schmidt Benoni in order to offer a new perspective, with lesser known positions. The lines divide into two main parts:   A.  3...g6   B.  3...b5  Both of which are well known and popular amongst Benoni and Benko players. }
