6... Be7 7. c3 { The e4-push is in the air. } 7... Nc6 8. e4
{ Uncharacteristically, we ignore Black's ...Nb4 idea here. } 8... cxd4 9. cxd4
Nb4 10. Bb1 Ba6 11. Re1 Nd3 12. Bxd3 Bxd3
{ Black has the bishop pair and even a strong bishop on d3. Here, though, time is of the essence. White wastes none and grasps the initiative. }
13. d5 { Threatening d6 ! } 13... Qc8 14. d6 Bd8 15. Ne5 Bc2 16. Qf3 O-O 17. b3
{ The c2-bishop is simply a bad piece. } *

