[Black "Conclusion"]
[Result "*"]

1. d4 Nf6 2. Nf3 e6 3. e3 b6 4. Bd3 Bb7 5. O-O c5
{ This is a typical plan that many Queen's and Nimzo-Indian players employ.Hence, as it is a rather popular choice nowadays, it found its way into this book.I have therefore presented two setups for White:  A.   6.Nbd2  , leading to lesser known paths which may sometimes transpose to different systems, the London for instance.  B.   6.c4  , a straightforward attempt, which White wants to complement with  Nc3  and a potential  d5.  If successfully carried out, this can lead to an early advantage. }
