O-O 6. Nbd2 b6 7. Bd3
{ The starting point of the line. White will soon have to decide where to put the queen. }
7... Bb7 8. c3 Ne4 9. Qe2 d6 10. O-O-O Nd7 11. Rhg1 Kh8 12. g4 Qe8
{ The queen on e8 is important as it may end up on a4 to create an attack. As will become clear, it also supports the e5 push ! }
13. gxf5 exf5 14. h4 Ndf6 15. Ng5 Nd5 16. Ne6 Ndxc3
{ A very important theme in this line; Black simply must create threats. } 17.
bxc3 Nxc3 18. Qf1 Qa4 19. Rxg7 Bd5
{ This leads to a draw, which, of course, takes nothing away from the overall richness of the line. }
20. Rxe7 Nxa2+ 21. Kb2 Qb4+ 22. Ka1 Qc3+ 23. Kb1 Qb4+ *

