O-O 6. Nbd2 b6 7. Bd3
{ The starting point of the line. White will soon have to decide where to put the queen. }
7... Bb7 8. c3 Ne4 9. Rg1
{ A cunning move. White waits before committing the queen to a square and decides to open the g-file first. }
9... Kh8 { is probably best as the king will most likely end up on h8 anyway. }
10. g4 d6 11. gxf5 exf5 12. Qc2 Nxd2
{ Now that the structure is a little weakened, White forces Black to choose between d5 or taking on d2. }
13. Nxd2 Qd7 14. O-O-O Na6 { Black must react fast. } 15. h4 c5 16. Nb3 Rac8
17. dxc5 Nxc5 18. Nxc5 Rxc5 19. h5 b5 { with mutual chances. } *

